oai_dc:dc.dc:description: "The governing body of the Middle Temple is called the parliament; its orders, called minutes of parliament, are preserved in volumes called Parliament Books. Middle Temple Parliament Books survive from 1500, except that the second volume, for 1524–51, is lost (whence number ‘2’ is omitted from the sequence of shelfmarks)."
